    {
      "charEnd": 1033,
      "charStart": 745,
      "factId": "hz.web.eb212e096e9235b7.fact.2",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "Nearly every company with an API used by third party developers has implemented OAuth to enable people to build apps on top of it.</p>\\n<p>While OAuth is a great framework for this, the way it has ended up being used is much more centralized and closed than prior efforts like OpenID 1.",
