    },
    {
      "charEnd": 1551,
      "charStart": 1124,
      "factId": "hz.web.eb212e096e9235b7.fact.4",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "For example, if I want to build an app that can read someone's step count from FitBit, I have to first go register as a developer on FitBit's website in order to get API keys to use with their OAuth API.&#xA0;</p>\\n<p>This works okay for major services like Google, Twitter, Facebook, and even FitBit, but breaks down when you start to consider use cases like having someone's personal WordPress blog be its own OAuth server.",
